rows.name: Grade 1 Mild Adverse Event
rows.description: A type of adverse event that is usually transient and may require only minimal treatment or therapeutic intervention. The event does not generally interfere with usual activities of daily living.

rows.name: Grade 2 Moderate Adverse Event
rows.description: A type of adverse event that is usually alleviated with additional specific therapeutic intervention. The event interferes with usual activities of daily living, causing discomfort but poses no significant or permanent risk of harm to the research participant.

rows.name: Grade 3 Severe Adverse Event
rows.description: A type of adverse event that requires intensive therapeutic intervention. The event interrupts usual activities of daily living, or significantly affects clinical status. The event possesses a significant risk of harm to the research participant and hospitalization may be required.

rows.name: Grade 4 Life Threatening or Disabling Adverse Event
rows.description: An adverse event, and/or its immediate sequelae, which is associated with an imminent risk of death or which is associated with physical or mental disabilities that affect or limit the ability of a person to perform activities of daily living (eating, ambulation, toileting, etc.)

rows.name: Grade 5 Death Related to Adverse Event
rows.description: The termination of life as a result of an adverse event.

rows.name: Not Specified
rows.description: Adverse Event is not specified or not received. If no Adverse Event value is received, then this is the system default value.

rows.name: Age at enrollment
rows.description: Age Event is the Age at enrollment. In the case of a subject enrolled in multiple studies, this value is the minimum age for all the studies.

rows.name: Age at infection
rows.description: Age Event is the Age at infection.

rows.name: Age at initial treatment
rows.description: Age Event is the Age at initial treatment.

rows.name: Age at initial vaccine administration
rows.description: Age Event is the Age at initial vaccine administration.

rows.name: Age at Study Day 0
rows.description: Age Event is the Age at Study Day 0.

rows.name: Not Specified
rows.description: Age Event is not specified or not received. If no Age Event value is received, then this is the system default value.

rows.name: Other
rows.description: Age Event is some Other value not in CV Terms.

rows.name: Postmenstrual age
rows.description: Best estimate of the first day of last menstrual period to birth plus time elapsed from day of birth. [def-source: NCI][attr: NICHD]

rows.name: DK units/ml
rows.description: The NIDDK calibrators were tested together with dilutions of the WHO reference serum using harmonized assays on five occasions in the BDC, Bristol, and Munich laboratories and reported as WHO units/ml by calibration as previously described. For each of the NIDDK calibrators, the median value of the WHO units/ml obtained for the 15 measurements was assigned as its calibrator unit. The assigned units were termed digestive and kidney units (DK units)/ml.

rows.name: IU
rows.description: The unitage assigned by the WHO to International Biological Standards - substances, classed as biological according to the criteria provided by WHO Expert Committee on Biological Standardization (e.g. hormones, enzymes, and vaccines), to enable the results of biological and immunological assay procedures to be expressed in the same way throughout the world. The definition of an international unit is generally arbitrary and technical, and has to be officially approved by the International Conference for Unification of Formulae.

rows.name: IU/ml
rows.description: A unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milliliter of system volume.

rows.name: Not Specified
rows.description: No value provided. Not stated explicitly or in detail.

rows.name: optical density
rows.description: The measurement of the light transmitted through a sample for a given wavelength. [database_cross_reference: ISBN:038733341X]

rows.name: units/ml
rows.description: Enzyme Unit per Milliliter. Unit of catalytic activity concentration defined as activity equal to one enzyme unit per one milliliter of system volume.

rows.name: Australia
rows.description: Australia and all of its islands (for example, Groote Eylandt, Tasmania, etc).

rows.name: Europe
rows.description: An area bounded by Franz Joseph Land, Svalbard, Iceland, the northern coast of the Mediterranean and Black Seas, and those areas of Russia west of the Caspian Sea and Kazakhstan. Includes Mediterranean islands that are part of European nations, with the exception of Cyprus and islands that are part of Turkey.

rows.name: North Africa
rows.description: Nations on the African continent north of a line drawn between Nouadhibou in Mauritania and Djiubouti. Includes all of Western Sahara, Morocco, Algeria, Lyibia, Egypt, Eritrea, and Djibouti and northern areas of Mauritania, Mali, Niger, Chad, Sudan, and Ethiopia.

rows.name: North America
rows.description: Canada, the United States, Mexico, the Carribean, the Aleutian islands, and Greenland.

rows.name: North-East Asia
rows.description: Russia north and east of Kazakhstan (and associated islands), Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan, Kyrgyztan, Tajikistan, Mongolia, China east and north of Mongolia and east of the Bohai Sea, the Korean pennisula, and the islands of Japan.

rows.name: Oceania
rows.description: An area of the Pacific bounded by the Hawaiian Islands, Easter Island, the islands of New Zealand, the Sunda Islands, Madagascar, those areas of Borneo not part of Malaysia, and the Phillipines.

rows.name: Other
rows.description: This category is for populations derived from more than one of the other regions defined here.

rows.name: South America
rows.description: All of the South American and the Central American nations, and associated islands.

rows.name: South-East Asia
rows.description: China west and south of Mongolia, Taiwan, Vietnam, Laos, Cambodia, Thailand, Malaysia (including the Malaysian area of Borneo), Singapore, and Burma.

rows.name: South-West Asia
rows.description: Cyprus, Turkey (and associated islands), Georgia, Armenia, Azerbaijan, Syria, Lebanon, Israel, the Palestinian Territories, Jordan, the Saudi peninsula, Iraq, Kuwait, Iran, Turkmenistan, Afghanistan, Pakistan, India, Sri Lanka, and Bangladesh.

rows.name: Sub-Saharan Africa
rows.description: The area on the African continent south of the Sahara, defined by a line drawn between Nouadhibou in Mauritania and Djiubouti, and the islands associated with the nations of that area. Includes the southern areas of Mauritania, Mali, Niger, Chad, Sudan, and Ethiopia. Madagascar is not included in this region.

rows.name: cells/ul
rows.description: A unit of cell concentration expressed as a number of cells per unit volume equal to one microliter.

rows.name: MFI at 90th percentile
rows.description: Mean Fluorescence Intensity at 90th Percentile.  MFI : A unit of measure equal to the geometric mean fluorescence intensity of a log-normal distribution of fluorescence signals.

rows.name: Not Specified
rows.description: No value provided. Not stated explicitly or in detail.

rows.name: percentage
rows.description: A fraction or ratio with 100 understood as the denominator. e.g. percentage of a cell population of interest within a parent population

rows.name: stim/unstim fold change
rows.description: Fold change comparing stimulated vs unstimulated sample

rows.name: - ; basophil
rows.description: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has an irregularly shaped, pale-staining nucleus that is partially constricted into two lobes, and with cytoplasm that contains coarse, bluish-black granules of variable size. Basophils contain vasoactive amines such as histamine and serotonin, which are released on appropriate stimulation. A basophil is CD123-positive, CD193-positive, CD203c-positive, and FceRIa-positive.;Matures in the bone marrow and account for <1% of leukocytes in the peripheral blood, spleen, and bone marrow. Basophils are described as being CD11a-positive, CD11b-positive, CD13-positive, CD15-positive, CD18-positive, CD21-positive, CD25-positive, CD29-positive, CD35-positive, CD40-positive, CD40L-positive, CD44-positive, CD45R-negative, CD46-positive, CD49a-positive, CD49b-positive, CD49d-positive, CD55-positive, CD59-positive, CD62L-positive, CD63-positive, CD69-positive, CD90-negative, CD116-positive, CD117-negative, CD124-positive, CD125-positive, CD131-positive, CD161-positive, CD184-positive, CD191-positive, CD192-positive, CD197-positive, CD200R3-positive, CD218-positive, CD282-positive, CD284-positive, CD289-positive, CD290-positive, CD294-positive, natural killer cell receptor 2B4-positive, smad1-positive, CD3-negative, CD4-negative, CD7-negative, CD8-negative, CD14-negative, CD15-negative, CD16-negative, CD19-negative, CD20-negative, CD34-negative, CD36-negative, CD45R-negative, CD56-negative, CD57-negative, CD235a-negative, and GR1-negative. Transcription factors- GATA1-positive, PU.1-positive.

rows.name: - ; cell
rows.description: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.;The definition of cell is intended to represent all cells, and thus a cell is defined as a material entity and not an anatomical structure, which implies that it is part of an organism (or the entirety of one).

rows.name: - ; eosinophil
rows.description: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte with a nucleus that usually has two lobes connected by one or more slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing coarse, round granules that are uniform in size and which can be stained by the dye eosin. Eosinophils are CD9-positive, CD191-positive, and CD193-positive.;Eosinophils are also CD14-negative, CD32-positive, CD44-positive, CD48-positive, CD69-positive, CD192-negative, MBP1-positive, MBP2-positive, TLR2-negative, TLR4-negative, and lineage-negative (B220, CD2, CD14, CD19, CD56, CD71, CD117, CD123, CD235a (glycophorin A), and TER119). The cytokines IL-3, IL-5, and GM-CSF are involved in their development and differentiation. Usually considered CD16-negative, CD16 is observed on eosinophilic metamyelocyte.

rows.name: - ; granulocyte
rows.description: A leukocyte with abundant granules in the cytoplasm.

rows.name: - ; leukocyte
rows.description: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

rows.name: - ; leukocyte, platelet
rows.description: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.;A non-nucleated disk-shaped cell formed by extrusion from megakaryocytes, found in the blood of all mammals, and mainly involved in blood coagulation.;Platelets are reportedly CCR1-positive, CCR2-negative, CCR3-positive, CCR4-positive, CCR5-negative, CCR6-negative, CCR7-negative, CCR8-negative, CCR9-negative, CCR10-negative, CD16-positive, CD23-positive, CD32-positive, CD40-positive, CD41-positive CD42-positive, CD61-positive, CD62P-positive, CD64-positive, CD89-positive, CD102-positive, CD147-positive (activated platelets), CD154-positive (activated platelets), CD162-positive, CD209, CD282-positive, CD284-positive, CD289-positive, CD181-negative, CD182-negative, CD183-negative, CD184-positive, CLEC2-positive, GPVI-positive, JAMC-positive, PAR1-positive, PAR2-negative, PAR3-positive, PAR4-positive, TSP1-positive, and TXA2R-positive. Platelets can reportedly produce CCL2, CCL3, CCL5, CCL7, CCL17, CD40L, CXCL1, CXCL4, CXCL4L1, CXCL5, CXCL7, CXCL8, CXCL12, EGF, factor V, factor VII, factor XI, factor XIII, bFGF, histamine, IGF-1, IL-1beta, PAI-1, PDGF, plasminogen, protein S, serotonin, TGF-beta, TFPI, VEGF, and vWF.

rows.name: - ; lymphocyte
rows.description: A lymphocyte is a leukocyte commonly found in the blood and lymph that has the characteristics of a large nucleus, a neutral staining cytoplasm, and prominent heterochromatin.;Editors note: consider adding taxon constraint to vertebrata (PMID:18025161)

rows.name: - ; mature neutrophil
rows.description: A fully differentiated neutrophil, a granular leukocyte having a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes. They are produced in bone marrow at a rate of 5e10-10e10/day and have a half-life of 6-8 hours. Neutrophils are CD15-positive, CD16-positive, CD32-positive, CD43-positive, CD181-positive, and CD182-positive.;Neutrophils are also capable of secreting GRO-alpha, IL-1beta, IL-1ra, IL-3, IL-12, IP-10, MIG, MIP-1alpha, MIP-1beta, TGF-beta, TNF-alpha, VEGF, and anti-microbial peptides. They can positively influence the chemotaxis of basophils, T-cells, monocytes, macrophages, dendritic cells, and other neutrophils. Neutrophils are also CD35-positive, CD64-positive, CD89-positive, CD184-positive, and fMLP receptor-positive Ly-6G-positive (mouse), TLR2-low, TLR4-low, and lineage-negative (CD2, CD3, CD5, CD9, CD19, CD36, CD49d, CD56, CD61, CD235a (glycophorin-A)).

rows.name: - ; neutrophil
rows.description: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

rows.name: - ; PBMC
rows.description: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form found in the circulatory pool of blood.

rows.name: - ; platelet
rows.description: A non-nucleated disk-shaped cell formed by extrusion from megakaryocytes, found in the blood of all mammals, and mainly involved in blood coagulation.;Platelets are reportedly CCR1-positive, CCR2-negative, CCR3-positive, CCR4-positive, CCR5-negative, CCR6-negative, CCR7-negative, CCR8-negative, CCR9-negative, CCR10-negative, CD16-positive, CD23-positive, CD32-positive, CD40-positive, CD41-positive CD42-positive, CD61-positive, CD62P-positive, CD64-positive, CD89-positive, CD102-positive, CD147-positive (activated platelets), CD154-positive (activated platelets), CD162-positive, CD209, CD282-positive, CD284-positive, CD289-positive, CD181-negative, CD182-negative, CD183-negative, CD184-positive, CLEC2-positive, GPVI-positive, JAMC-positive, PAR1-positive, PAR2-negative, PAR3-positive, PAR4-positive, TSP1-positive, and TXA2R-positive. Platelets can reportedly produce CCL2, CCL3, CCL5, CCL7, CCL17, CD40L, CXCL1, CXCL4, CXCL4L1, CXCL5, CXCL7, CXCL8, CXCL12, EGF, factor V, factor VII, factor XI, factor XIII, bFGF, histamine, IGF-1, IL-1beta, PAI-1, PDGF, plasminogen, protein S, serotonin, TGF-beta, TFPI, VEGF, and vWF.

rows.name: - ; reticulocyte
rows.description: An immature erythrocyte that changes the protein composition of its plasma membrane by exosome formation and extrusion. The types of protein removed differ between species though removal of the transferrin receptor is apparent in mammals and birds.

rows.name: B ; B cell
rows.description: A lymphocyte of B lineage with the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, and capable of B cell mediated immunity.

rows.name: B ; class switched memory B cell
rows.description: A class switched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has undergone Ig class switching and therefore is IgM-negative on the cell surface. These cells are CD27-positive and have either IgG, IgE, or IgA on the cell surface.;Per DSD: Class switched memory B cells are also reportedly CD48-positive, CD229-positive, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: B ; IgD+ memory B cell
rows.description: An unswitched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has the phenotype IgM-positive, IgD-positive, CD27-positive, CD138-negative, IgG-negative, IgE-negative, and IgA-negative.

rows.name: B ; IgD- memory B cell
rows.description: A memory B cell that lacks expression of surface IgD.

rows.name: B ; IgG memory B cell
rows.description: An IgG memory B cell is a class switched memory B cell that is class switched and expresses IgG on the cell surface.

rows.name: B ; immature B cell
rows.description: An immature B cell is a B cell that has the phenotype surface IgM-positive and surface IgD-negative, and have not undergone class immunoglobulin class switching or peripheral encounter with antigen and activation.;Immature B cells are also reportedly CD5-positive, CD10-positive, CD19-positive, CD20-positive, CD21-positive, CD22-positive, CD24-positive, CD25-negative, CD27-negative, CD34-negative, CD38-positive, CD40-positive, CD43-negative, CD45-positive, CD48-positive, CD53-positive, CD79a-positive, CD80-negative, CD81-positive, CD86-negative, CD95-negative, CD127-negative, CD138-negative, CD185-positive, CD196-positive, MHCII/HLA-DR-positive, RAG-positive, TdT-negative, Vpre-B-negative, and preBCR-negative. Transcription factors expressed: Pax5-positive.

rows.name: B ; marginal zone B cell
rows.description: A mature B cell that is located in the marginal zone of the spleen with the phenotype CD23-negative and CD21-positive and expressing a B cell receptor usually reactive to bacterial cell wall components or senescent self components such as oxidized-LDL. This cell type is also described as being CD19-positive, B220-positive, IgM-high, AA4-negative, CD35-high.;MZ B cells are reportedly CD1-positive (mice), CD20-positive, CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD150-positive, CD229-positive, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: B ; mature B cell
rows.description: A B cell that is mature, having left the bone marrow. Initially, these cells are IgM-positive and IgD-positive, and they can be activated by antigen.;Mature B cells are also reportedly CD10-negative, CD19-positive, CD22-positive, CD34-negative, CD48-positive, CD79a-positive, CD84-positive, CD127-negative, CD352-positive, RAG-negative, TdT-negative, Vpre-B-negative, and pre-BCR-negative. Transcription factors expressed: Pax5-positive.

rows.name: B ; memory B cell
rows.description: A memory B cell is a mature B cell that is long-lived, readily activated upon re-encounter of its antigenic determinant, and has been selected for expression of higher affinity immunoglobulin. This cell type has the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, MHC Class II-positive, and CD138-negative.

rows.name: B ; naive B cell
rows.description: A naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, CD20-positive, CD27-negative and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

rows.name: B ; plasma cell
rows.description: A terminally differentiated, post-mitotic, antibody secreting cell of the B cell lineage with the phenotype CD138-positive, surface immunonoglobulin-negative, and MHC Class II-negative. Plasma cells are oval or round with extensive rough endoplasmic reticulum, a well-developed Golgi apparatus, and a round nucleus having a characteristic cartwheel heterochromatin pattern and are devoted to producing large amounts of immunoglobulin.;Plasma cells develop in the spleen and migrate to the bone marrow. Plasma cells are also reportedly CD5-negative, CD10-negative, CD19-positive, CD20-negative, CD21-negative, CD22-negative, CD23-negative, CD24-negative, CD25-negative, CD27-positive, CD34-negative, CD38-positive, CD40-positive, CD43-positive, CD45-positive, CD48-positive, CD53-low, CD80-negative, CD81-positive, CD86-positive, CD95-positive, CD196-negative, CD229-positive, CD270-positive, CD352-positive, CD361-positive, and IgD-negative. Transcription factors: BLIMP1-positive, IRF4-positive, PAX5-negative, SpiB-negative, Ets1-negative, and XBP1-positive.

rows.name: B ; plasmablast
rows.description: An activated mature (naive or memory) B cell that is secreting immunoglobulin, typified by being CD27-positive, CD38-positive, CD138-negative.

rows.name: B ; T1 B cell
rows.description: A transitional stage B cell that migrates from the bone marrow into the peripheral circulation, and finally to the spleen. This cell type has the phenotype surface IgM-positive, surface IgD-negative, CD21-negative, CD23-negative, and CD62L-negative, and CD93-positive. This cell type has also been described as IgM-high, CD19-positive, B220-positive, AA4-positive, and CD23-negative.;T1 B cells are also reportedly CD10-negative/positive??, CD20-positive, CD24-positive, CD38-positive, CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD150-positive, CD244-negative, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: B ; T2 B cell
rows.description: A transitional stage B cell that has the phenotype surface IgM-positive, surface IgD-postive, CD21-positive, CD23-positive, CD62L-negative, CD93-positive and is located in the splenic B follicles. This cell type has also been described as IgM-high, CD19-positive, B220-positive, AA4-positive, and CD23-positive.;T2 B cells are also reportedly CD20-positive, CD24-positive, CD38-positive, CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD150-positive, CD244-negative, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: B ; transitional B cell
rows.description: An immature B cell of an intermediate stage between the pre-B cell stage and the mature naive stage with the phenotype surface IgM-positive and CD19-positive, and are subject to the process of B cell selection. A transitional B cell migrates from the bone marrow into the peripheral circulation, and then to the spleen.

rows.name: DC ; CD1c-positive myeloid dendritic cell
rows.description: A myeloid dendritic cell found in the blood that is CD1c-positive.;Normally represent 10-20% of peripheral blood mDCs (human). They are also CD281-positive (TLR1), CD282-positive (TLR2), CD283-positive (TLR3), CD284-positive (TLR4), CD285-positive (TLR5), CD286-positive (TLR6), CD288-positive (TLR8), and CD290-positive (TLR10) [PMID:20204387]. Upon TLR stimulation, these cells were potent producers of CXCL8 (IL-8), while producing little TNF-alpha.

rows.name: DC ; dendritic cell
rows.description: A cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation. These cells are lineage negative (CD3-negative, CD19-negative, CD34-negative, and CD56-negative).

rows.name: DC ; myeloid dendritic cell
rows.description: A dendritic cell of the myeloid lineage.

rows.name: DC ; plasmacytoid dendritic cell
rows.description: A dendritic cell type of distinct morphology, localization, and surface marker expression (CD123-positive) from other dendritic cell types and associated with early stage immune responses, particularly the release of physiologically abundant amounts of type I interferons in response to infection.

rows.name: M ; CD14-positive monocyte
rows.description: A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.;This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'monocyte'. Note that while CD14 is considered a reliable marker for human monocytes, it is only expressed on approximately 85% of mouse monocytes.

rows.name: M ; CD16+ monocyte
rows.description: A CD14-positive monocyte that is also CD16-positive and CCR2-negative.

rows.name: M ; CD16- monocyte
rows.description: A classical monocyte that is CD14-positive, CD16-negative, CD64-positive, CD163-positive.

rows.name: M ; monocyte
rows.description: Myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

rows.name: NK ; CD16+ CD56+  NK cell
rows.description: A mature natural killer cell that has the phenotype CD56-low, CD16-positive and which is capable of cytotoxicity and cytokine production.

rows.name: NK ; CD16- CD56bright NK cell
rows.description: NK cell that has the phenotype CD56-bright, CD16-negative, and CD84-positive with the function to secrete interferon-gamma but is not cytotoxic.

rows.name: NK ; NK cell
rows.description: A lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors and also regulate immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

rows.name: T ; activated CCR4+ Treg
rows.description: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta T regulatory cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, indicating recent activation.

rows.name: T ; activated CD4+ T cell
rows.description: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

rows.name: T ; activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
rows.description: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

rows.name: T ; activated CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A recently activated CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, CCR7-negative, and CD25-positive.

rows.name: T ; CCR4+ Treg
rows.description: A naive regulatory T cell with the phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-negative.

rows.name: T ; CD4+ T cell
rows.description: A mature alpha-beta T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD4 coreceptor.

rows.name: T ; CD4-positive helper T cell
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that cooperates with other lymphocytes via direct contact or cytokine release to initiate a variety of immune functions.

rows.name: T ; CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A T cell expressing an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD8 coreceptor.

rows.name: T ; central memory CD4+ T cell
rows.description: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: T ; central memory CD8+ T cell
rows.description: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: T ; effector CD4+ T cell
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

rows.name: T ; effector CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

rows.name: T ; effector memory CD4+ T cell
rows.description: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: T ; effector memory CD8+ T cell
rows.description: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: T ; gamma-delta T cell
rows.description: A T cell that expresses a gamma-delta T cell receptor complex.;Note that gamma-delta T cells have both thymic and extrathymic differentiation pathways.

rows.name: T ; helper T cell
rows.description: A effector T cell that provides help in the form of secreted cytokines to other immune cells.

rows.name: T ; memory CCR4+ Treg
rows.description: A memory regulatory T cell with phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-positive.

rows.name: T ; naive CCR4+ Treg
rows.description: A naive regulatory T cell with the phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-negative.

rows.name: T ; naive CD4+ T cell
rows.description: An antigen inexperienced CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive and CD62L-positive. This cell type develops in the thymus. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high, and CD44-low.

rows.name: T ; naive CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has not experienced activation via antigen contact and has the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CCR7-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

rows.name: T ; naive T cell
rows.description: Mature T cell not yet exposed to antigen with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD45RA-positive, and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

rows.name: T ; NK T cell
rows.description: A mature alpha-beta T cell of a distinct lineage that bears natural killer markers and a T cell receptor specific for a limited set of ligands. NK T cells have activation and regulatory roles particularly early in an immune response.

rows.name: T ; non-Tc1/Tc17 CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.;A CD8-positive, alpha-beta positive T cell expressing GATA-3 and secreting IL-4.

rows.name: T ; non-Th1/Th17  CD4+ T cell
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype GATA-3-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, and is capable of producing interleukin-4.

rows.name: T ; regulatory T cell
rows.description: A T cell which regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.;This cell type may express FoxP3 and CD25 and secretes IL-10 and TGF-beta.

rows.name: T ; T cell
rows.description: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

rows.name: T ; T follicular helper cell
rows.description: A CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cell located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses is BCL6-high, ICOS-high and PD1-high, and stimulates follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production.

rows.name: T ; Tc1 CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta positive T cell that has the phenotype T-bet-positive, eomesodermin-positive, CXCR3-positive, CCR6-negative, and is capable of producing interferon-gamma.

rows.name: T ; Tc17 CD8+ T cell
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, CCR5-high, CD45RA-negative, and capable of producing IL-17 and some IFNg.

rows.name: T ; Th1 CD4+ T cell
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype T-bet-positive, CXCR3-positive, CCR6-negative, and is capable of producing interferon-gamma.

rows.name: T ; Th17 CD4+ T cell
rows.description: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, and capable of producing IL-17.

rows.name: T ; Treg
rows.description: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta T cell that regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.

rows.name: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form found in the circulatory pool of blood.
rows.description: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form found in the circulatory pool of blood.

rows.description: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.;A non-nucleated disk-shaped cell formed by extrusion from megakaryocytes, found in the blood of all mammals, and mainly involved in blood coagulation.;Platelets are reportedly CCR1-positive, CCR2-negative, CCR3-positive, CCR4-positive, CCR5-negative, CCR6-negative, CCR7-negative, CCR8-negative, CCR9-negative, CCR10-negative, CD16-positive, CD23-positive, CD32-positive, CD40-positive, CD41-positive CD42-positive, CD61-positive, CD62P-positive, CD64-positive, CD89-positive, CD102-positive, CD147-positive (activated platelets), CD154-positive (activated platelets), CD162-positive, CD209, CD282-positive, CD284-positive, CD289-positive, CD181-negative, CD182-negative, CD183-negative, CD184-positive, CLEC2-positive, GPVI-positive, JAMC-positive, PAR1-positive, PAR2-negative, PAR3-positive, PAR4-positive, TSP1-positive, and TXA2R-positive. Platelets can reportedly produce CCL2, CCL3, CCL5, CCL7, CCL17, CD40L, CXCL1, CXCL4, CXCL4L1, CXCL5, CXCL7, CXCL8, CXCL12, EGF, factor V, factor VII, factor XI, factor XIII, bFGF, histamine, IGF-1, IL-1beta, PAI-1, PDGF, plasminogen, protein S, serotonin, TGF-beta, TFPI, VEGF, and vWF.

rows.name: CCR1+, CCR2-, CCR3+, CCR4+, CCR5-, CCR6-, CCR7-, CCR8-, CCR9-, CCR10-, CD16+, CD23+, CD32+, CD40+, CD41+ CD42+, CD61+, CD62P+, CD64+, CD89+, CD102+, CD147+, CD154+, CD162+, CD209, CD282+, CD284+, CD289+, CD181-, CD182-, CD183-, CD184+, CLEC2+, GPVI+, JAMC+, PAR1+, PAR2-, PAR3+, PAR4+, TSP1+, TXA2R+
rows.description: A non-nucleated disk-shaped cell formed by extrusion from megakaryocytes, found in the blood of all mammals, and mainly involved in blood coagulation.;Platelets are reportedly CCR1-positive, CCR2-negative, CCR3-positive, CCR4-positive, CCR5-negative, CCR6-negative, CCR7-negative, CCR8-negative, CCR9-negative, CCR10-negative, CD16-positive, CD23-positive, CD32-positive, CD40-positive, CD41-positive CD42-positive, CD61-positive, CD62P-positive, CD64-positive, CD89-positive, CD102-positive, CD147-positive (activated platelets), CD154-positive (activated platelets), CD162-positive, CD209, CD282-positive, CD284-positive, CD289-positive, CD181-negative, CD182-negative, CD183-negative, CD184-positive, CLEC2-positive, GPVI-positive, JAMC-positive, PAR1-positive, PAR2-negative, PAR3-positive, PAR4-positive, TSP1-positive, and TXA2R-positive. Platelets can reportedly produce CCL2, CCL3, CCL5, CCL7, CCL17, CD40L, CXCL1, CXCL4, CXCL4L1, CXCL5, CXCL7, CXCL8, CXCL12, EGF, factor V, factor VII, factor XI, factor XIII, bFGF, histamine, IGF-1, IL-1beta, PAI-1, PDGF, plasminogen, protein S, serotonin, TGF-beta, TFPI, VEGF, and vWF.

rows.name: CCR7+, CD45RA+, CD127+, CD25-, CD62Lhi, and CD44lo
rows.description: Mature T cell not yet exposed to antigen with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD45RA-positive, and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

rows.name: CD10-, CD19+, CD22+, CD34-, CD48+, CD79a+, CD84+, CD127-, CD352+, RAG-, TdT-, Vpre-B-, pre-BCR-
rows.description: A B cell that is mature, having left the bone marrow. Initially, these cells are IgM-positive and IgD-positive, and they can be activated by antigen.;Mature B cells are also reportedly CD10-negative, CD19-positive, CD22-positive, CD34-negative, CD48-positive, CD79a-positive, CD84-positive, CD127-negative, CD352-positive, RAG-negative, TdT-negative, Vpre-B-negative, and pre-BCR-negative. Transcription factors expressed: Pax5-positive.

rows.name: CD123+, CD193+, CD203c+, FceRIa+
rows.description: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has an irregularly shaped, pale-staining nucleus that is partially constricted into two lobes, and with cytoplasm that contains coarse, bluish-black granules of variable size. Basophils contain vasoactive amines such as histamine and serotonin, which are released on appropriate stimulation. A basophil is CD123-positive, CD193-positive, CD203c-positive, and FceRIa-positive.;Matures in the bone marrow and account for <1% of leukocytes in the peripheral blood, spleen, and bone marrow. Basophils are described as being CD11a-positive, CD11b-positive, CD13-positive, CD15-positive, CD18-positive, CD21-positive, CD25-positive, CD29-positive, CD35-positive, CD40-positive, CD40L-positive, CD44-positive, CD45R-negative, CD46-positive, CD49a-positive, CD49b-positive, CD49d-positive, CD55-positive, CD59-positive, CD62L-positive, CD63-positive, CD69-positive, CD90-negative, CD116-positive, CD117-negative, CD124-positive, CD125-positive, CD131-positive, CD161-positive, CD184-positive, CD191-positive, CD192-positive, CD197-positive, CD200R3-positive, CD218-positive, CD282-positive, CD284-positive, CD289-positive, CD290-positive, CD294-positive, natural killer cell receptor 2B4-positive, smad1-positive, CD3-negative, CD4-negative, CD7-negative, CD8-negative, CD14-negative, CD15-negative, CD16-negative, CD19-negative, CD20-negative, CD34-negative, CD36-negative, CD45R-negative, CD56-negative, CD57-negative, CD235a-negative, and GR1-negative. Transcription factors- GATA1-positive, PU.1-positive.

rows.name: CD138+, CD5-, CD10-, CD19+, CD20-, CD21-, CD22-, CD23-, CD24-, CD25-, CD27+, CD34-, CD38+, CD40+, CD43+, CD45+, CD48+, CD53lo, CD80-, CD81+, CD86+, CD95+, CD196-, CD229+, CD270+, CD352+, CD361+, and IgD-

Plasma cells are oval or round with extensive rough endoplasmic reticulum, a well-developed Golgi apparatus, and a round nucleus having a characteristic cartwheel heterochromatin pattern and are devoted to producing large amounts of immunoglobulin.;Plasma cells develop in the spleen and migrate to the bone marrow. Plasma cells are also reportedly CD5-negative, CD10-negative, CD19-positive, CD20-negative, CD21-negative, CD22-negative, CD23-negative, CD24-negative, CD25-negative, CD27-positive, CD34-negative, CD38-positive, CD40-positive, CD43-positive, CD45-positive, CD48-positive, CD53-low, CD80-negative, CD81-positive, CD86-positive, CD95-positive, CD196-negative, CD229-positive, CD270-positive, CD352-positive, CD361-positive, and IgD-negative. Transcription factors: BLIMP1-positive, IRF4-positive, PAX5-negative, SpiB-negative, Ets1-negative, and XBP1-positive.

rows.name: CD14+
rows.description: A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.;This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'monocyte'. Note that while CD14 is considered a reliable marker for human monocytes, it is only expressed on approximately 85% of mouse monocytes.

rows.name: CD15+, CD16+, CD32+, CD43+, CD181+, CD182+
rows.description: A fully differentiated neutrophil, a granular leukocyte having a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes. They are produced in bone marrow at a rate of 5e10-10e10/day and have a half-life of 6-8 hours. Neutrophils are CD15-positive, CD16-positive, CD32-positive, CD43-positive, CD181-positive, and CD182-positive.;Neutrophils are also capable of secreting GRO-alpha, IL-1beta, IL-1ra, IL-3, IL-12, IP-10, MIG, MIP-1alpha, MIP-1beta, TGF-beta, TNF-alpha, VEGF, and anti-microbial peptides. They can positively influence the chemotaxis of basophils, T-cells, monocytes, macrophages, dendritic cells, and other neutrophils. Neutrophils are also CD35-positive, CD64-positive, CD89-positive, CD184-positive, and fMLP receptor-positive Ly-6G-positive (mouse), TLR2-low, TLR4-low, and lineage-negative (CD2, CD3, CD5, CD9, CD19, CD36, CD49d, CD56, CD61, CD235a (glycophorin-A)).

rows.name: CD1c+, CD281+, CD282+, CD283+, CD284+, CD285+, CD286+, CD288+, CD290+
rows.description: A myeloid dendritic cell found in the blood that is CD1c-positive.;Normally represent 10-20% of peripheral blood mDCs (human). They are also CD281-positive (TLR1), CD282-positive (TLR2), CD283-positive (TLR3), CD284-positive (TLR4), CD285-positive (TLR5), CD286-positive (TLR6), CD288-positive (TLR8), and CD290-positive (TLR10) [PMID:20204387]. Upon TLR stimulation, these cells were potent producers of CXCL8 (IL-8), while producing little TNF-alpha.

rows.name: CD23-, CD21+, CD19+, B220+, IgM-hi, AA4-, CD35-hi
rows.description: A mature B cell that is located in the marginal zone of the spleen with the phenotype CD23-negative and CD21-positive and expressing a B cell receptor usually reactive to bacterial cell wall components or senescent self components such as oxidized-LDL. This cell type is also described as being CD19-positive, B220-positive, IgM-high, AA4-negative, CD35-high.;MZ B cells are reportedly CD1-positive (mice), CD20-positive, CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD150-positive, CD229-positive, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: CD27+, CD48+, CD229+, CD352+
rows.description: A class switched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has undergone Ig class switching and therefore is IgM-negative on the cell surface. These cells are CD27-positive and have either IgG, IgE, or IgA on the cell surface.;Per DSD: Class switched memory B cells are also reportedly CD48-positive, CD229-positive, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: CD3+
rows.description: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+
rows.description: A mature alpha-beta T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD4 coreceptor.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD127lo, CD25+
rows.description: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta T cell that regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD127lo, CD25+, CCR4+
rows.description: A naive regulatory T cell with the phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-negative.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD127lo, CD25+, CCR4+, CD45RO+
rows.description: A memory regulatory T cell with phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-positive.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD127lo, CD25+, CCR4+, CD45RO-
rows.description: A naive regulatory T cell with the phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-negative.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD127lo, CD25+, CCR4+, HLA-DR+
rows.description: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta T regulatory cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, indicating recent activation.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CCR7+, CD45RA+
rows.description: An antigen inexperienced CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive and CD62L-positive. This cell type develops in the thymus. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high, and CD44-low.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CCR7+, CD45RA-
rows.description: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CCR7-, CD45RA+
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CCR7-, CD45RA-
rows.description: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CD38+, HLA-DR+
rows.description: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CXCR3+, CCR6-
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype T-bet-positive, CXCR3-positive, CCR6-negative, and is capable of producing interferon-gamma.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CXCR3-, CCR6+
rows.description: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, and capable of producing IL-17.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4+, CD8-, CXCR3-, CCR6-
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype GATA-3-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, and is capable of producing interleukin-4.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CCR7+, CD45RA+
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has not experienced activation via antigen contact and has the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CCR7-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CCR7+, CD45RA-
rows.description: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CCR7-, CD45RA+
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CCR7-, CD45RA-
rows.description: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CD38+, HLA-DR+
rows.description: A recently activated CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, CCR7-negative, and CD25-positive.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CXCR3+, CCR6-
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta positive T cell that has the phenotype T-bet-positive, eomesodermin-positive, CXCR3-positive, CCR6-negative, and is capable of producing interferon-gamma.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CXCR3-, CCR6+
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, CCR5-high, CD45RA-negative, and capable of producing IL-17 and some IFNg.

rows.name: CD3+, CD4-, CD8+, CXCR3-, CCR6-
rows.description: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.;A CD8-positive, alpha-beta positive T cell expressing GATA-3 and secreting IL-4.

rows.name: CD3+, CD56+, CD14-, CD33-
rows.description: A mature alpha-beta T cell of a distinct lineage that bears natural killer markers and a T cell receptor specific for a limited set of ligands. NK T cells have activation and regulatory roles particularly early in an immune response.

rows.name: CD3+, CD8+
rows.description: A T cell expressing an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD8 coreceptor.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+ , CD20+
rows.description: A lymphocyte of B lineage with the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, and capable of B cell mediated immunity.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+, CD20+, CD24hi, CD38hi
rows.description: An immature B cell of an intermediate stage between the pre-B cell stage and the mature naive stage with the phenotype surface IgM-positive and CD19-positive, and are subject to the process of B cell selection. A transitional B cell migrates from the bone marrow into the peripheral circulation, and then to the spleen.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+, CD20+, CD27+
rows.description: A memory B cell is a mature B cell that is long-lived, readily activated upon re-encounter of its antigenic determinant, and has been selected for expression of higher affinity immunoglobulin. This cell type has the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, MHC Class II-positive, and CD138-negative.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+, CD20+, CD27+, IgD+
rows.description: An unswitched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has the phenotype IgM-positive, IgD-positive, CD27-positive, CD138-negative, IgG-negative, IgE-negative, and IgA-negative.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+, CD20+, CD27+, IgD-
rows.description: A memory B cell that lacks expression of surface IgD.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+, CD20+, CD27-, IgD+
rows.description: A naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, CD20-positive, CD27-negative and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19+, CD20-, CD27hi, CD38hi
rows.description: An activated mature (naive or memory) B cell that is secreting immunoglobulin, typified by being CD27-positive, CD38-positive, CD138-negative.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14+
rows.description: Myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14+, CD16+
rows.description: A CD14-positive monocyte that is also CD16-positive and CCR2-negative.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14+, CD16-
rows.description: A classical monocyte that is CD14-positive, CD16-negative, CD64-positive, CD163-positive.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14-, CD16-, CD56-, HLA-DR+
rows.description: A cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation. These cells are lineage negative (CD3-negative, CD19-negative, CD34-negative, and CD56-negative).

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14-, CD16-, CD56-, HLA-DR+, CD11c+, CD123-
rows.description: A dendritic cell of the myeloid lineage.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14-, CD16-, CD56-, HLA-DR+, CD11c-, CD123+
rows.description: A dendritic cell type of distinct morphology, localization, and surface marker expression (CD123-positive) from other dendritic cell types and associated with early stage immune responses, particularly the release of physiologically abundant amounts of type I interferons in response to infection.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14-, HLA-DR-, CD16+, CD56+
rows.description: A mature natural killer cell that has the phenotype CD56-low, CD16-positive and which is capable of cytotoxicity and cytokine production.

rows.name: CD3-, CD19-, CD20-, CD14-, HLA-DR-, CD16-, CD56++
rows.description: NK cell that has the phenotype CD56-bright, CD16-negative, and CD84-positive with the function to secrete interferon-gamma but is not cytotoxic.

rows.name: CD3-, CD56+
rows.description: A lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors and also regulate immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

rows.name: CD4+
rows.description: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that cooperates with other lymphocytes via direct contact or cytokine release to initiate a variety of immune functions.

rows.name: CD4+, CD69+, CD62L-, CD127-, and CD25+
rows.description: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

rows.name: CD4+, CXCR5+, CCR7-
rows.description: A CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cell located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses is BCL6-high, ICOS-high and PD1-high, and stimulates follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production.

rows.name: CD5+, CD10+, CD19+, CD20+, CD21+, CD22+, CD24+, CD25-, CD27-, CD34-, CD38+, CD40+, CD43-, CD45+, CD48+, CD53+, CD79a+, CD80-, CD81+, CD86-, CD95-, CD127-, CD138-, CD185+, CD196+, MHCII/HLA-DR+, RAG+, TdT-, Vpre-B-, preBCR-
rows.description: An immature B cell is a B cell that has the phenotype surface IgM-positive and surface IgD-negative, and have not undergone class immunoglobulin class switching or peripheral encounter with antigen and activation.;Immature B cells are also reportedly CD5-positive, CD10-positive, CD19-positive, CD20-positive, CD21-positive, CD22-positive, CD24-positive, CD25-negative, CD27-negative, CD34-negative, CD38-positive, CD40-positive, CD43-negative, CD45-positive, CD48-positive, CD53-positive, CD79a-positive, CD80-negative, CD81-positive, CD86-negative, CD95-negative, CD127-negative, CD138-negative, CD185-positive, CD196-positive, MHCII/HLA-DR-positive, RAG-positive, TdT-negative, Vpre-B-negative, and preBCR-negative. Transcription factors expressed: Pax5-positive.

rows.name: CD9+, CD191+, CD193+, CD14-, CD32+, CD44+, CD48+, CD69+, CD192-, MBP1+, MBP2+, TLR2-, TLR4-
rows.description: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte with a nucleus that usually has two lobes connected by one or more slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing coarse, round granules that are uniform in size and which can be stained by the dye eosin. Eosinophils are CD9-positive, CD191-positive, and CD193-positive.;Eosinophils are also CD14-negative, CD32-positive, CD44-positive, CD48-positive, CD69-positive, CD192-negative, MBP1-positive, MBP2-positive, TLR2-negative, TLR4-negative, and lineage-negative (B220, CD2, CD14, CD19, CD56, CD71, CD117, CD123, CD235a (glycophorin A), and TER119). The cytokines IL-3, IL-5, and GM-CSF are involved in their development and differentiation. Usually considered CD16-negative, CD16 is observed on eosinophilic metamyelocyte.

rows.name: Cell
rows.description: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.;The definition of cell is intended to represent all cells, and thus a cell is defined as a material entity and not an anatomical structure, which implies that it is part of an organism (or the entirety of one).

rows.name: FoxP3, CD25, IL-10, TGF-beta
rows.description: A T cell which regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.;This cell type may express FoxP3 and CD25 and secretes IL-10 and TGF-beta.

rows.name: gamma-delta T cell
rows.description: A T cell that expresses a gamma-delta T cell receptor complex.;Note that gamma-delta T cells have both thymic and extrathymic differentiation pathways.

rows.name: Granulocyte
rows.description: A leukocyte with abundant granules in the cytoplasm.

rows.name: Helper T cell
rows.description: A effector T cell that provides help in the form of secreted cytokines to other immune cells.

rows.name: IgD+, CD21+, CD23+, CD62L-, CD93+
rows.description: A transitional stage B cell that has the phenotype surface IgM-positive, surface IgD-postive, CD21-positive, CD23-positive, CD62L-negative, CD93-positive and is located in the splenic B follicles. This cell type has also been described as IgM-high, CD19-positive, B220-positive, AA4-positive, and CD23-positive.;T2 B cells are also reportedly CD20-positive, CD24-positive, CD38-positive, CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD150-positive, CD244-negative, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: IgD-, CD21-, CD23-, and CD62L-, CD93+
rows.description: A transitional stage B cell that migrates from the bone marrow into the peripheral circulation, and finally to the spleen. This cell type has the phenotype surface IgM-positive, surface IgD-negative, CD21-negative, CD23-negative, and CD62L-negative, and CD93-positive. This cell type has also been described as IgM-high, CD19-positive, B220-positive, AA4-positive, and CD23-negative.;T1 B cells are also reportedly CD10-negative/positive??, CD20-positive, CD24-positive, CD38-positive, CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD150-positive, CD244-negative, and CD352-positive.

rows.name: IgG memory B cell
rows.description: An IgG memory B cell is a class switched memory B cell that is class switched and expresses IgG on the cell surface.

rows.name: Immature Erythrocyte
rows.description: An immature erythrocyte that changes the protein composition of its plasma membrane by exosome formation and extrusion. The types of protein removed differ between species though removal of the transferrin receptor is apparent in mammals and birds.

rows.name: Leukocyte
rows.description: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

rows.name: Living cells gated from dead cells
Lymphocyte
rows.description: A lymphocyte is a leukocyte commonly found in the blood and lymph that has the characteristics of a large nucleus, a neutral staining cytoplasm, and prominent heterochromatin.;Editors note: consider adding taxon constraint to vertebrata (PMID:18025161)

rows.name: Neutrophil
rows.description: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

DK units/ml
rows.description: The NIDDK calibrators were tested together with dilutions of the WHO reference serum using harmonized assays on five occasions in the BDC, Bristol, and Munich laboratories and reported as WHO units/ml by calibration as previously described. For each of the NIDDK calibrators, the median value of the WHO units/ml obtained for the 15 measurements was assigned as its calibrator unit. The assigned units were termed digestive and kidney units (DK units)/ml.

rows.name: IU/ml
rows.description: A unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milliliter of system volume.

rows.name: Not Specified
rows.description: No value provided. Not stated explicitly or in detail.

rows.name: optical density
rows.description: The measurement of the light transmitted through a sample for a given wavelength. [database_cross_reference: ISBN:038733341X]

rows.name: units/ml
rows.description: Enzyme Unit per Milliliter. Unit of catalytic activity concentration defined as activity equal to one enzyme unit per one milliliter of system volume.

rows.name: Exclusion
rows.description: Exclusion Criterion used to evaluate whether a subject is a candidate for exclusion in a study.

rows.name: Inclusion

rows.name: Aging ; C16269

rows.description: Clinically isolated syndrome (CIS) is one of the MS disease courses. rows.name: cystic kidney disease ; DOID:2975
rows.description: Polycystic kidney disease (PKD) is an inherited disorder in which clusters of cysts develop primarily within your kidneys, causing your kidneys to enlarge and lose function over time. rows.name: dengue disease ; DOID:12205

rows.name: dengue hemorrhagic fever ; DOID:12206

rows.name: diphtheria ; DOID:11405

Diphtheria toxin spreads through the bloodstream and can lead to potentially life-threatening complications that affect other organs of the body, such as the heart and kidneys.

Confluent lesions often cover the entire face, the crook of the elbow in the antecubital fossa, and behind the knee in the popliteal fossa. Radiation Sickness Syndrome ; NCIT:C50723
rows.description: The complex of symptoms characterizing the disease known as radiation injury, resulting from excessive exposure (greater than 200 rads or 2 gray) of the whole body (or large part) to ionizing radiation. The earliest of these symptoms are nausea, fatigue, vomiting, and diarrhea, which may be followed by epilation, hemorrhage, inflammation of the mouth and throat, and general loss of energy. In severe cases, where the radiation exposure has been approximately 1000 Rad (10 gray) or more, death may occur within two to four weeks. Those who survive six weeks after the receipt of a single large dose of radiation to the whole body may generally be expected to recover. (U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission).
